name: Kosciuszko
hint: The highest mountain on the Australian mainland, in the Snowy Mountains of New South Wales

name: Cook/Aoraki
hint: New Zealand's highest mountain, in the Southern Alps of the South Island, sacred to Maori people

name: Wilhelm
hint: The highest mountain in Papua New Guinea and the highest in Oceania outside Indonesia

name: Giluwe
hint: The second-highest mountain in Papua New Guinea, an extinct volcano and one of the highest volcanoes in Oceania

name: Ruapehu
hint: The highest mountain in New Zealand's North Island, an active stratovolcano with a crater lake

name: Taranaki
hint: A symmetrical volcanic cone on New Zealand's North Island, also known as Mount Egmont

name: Bogong
hint: The highest mountain in the state of Victoria, Australia, in the Alpine National Park

name: Ossa
hint: The highest mountain in Tasmania, Australia, located in the Cradle Mountain-Lake St Clair National Park
